      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BELL MAC MAGIC (4) missed the frame last time when fifth (18.73) in a Grade 5 at Dubbo after a slow start and settling well off the pace. Has a good record at this journey. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. Can make amends. TRALEE NADIA (7) has shown good improvement at her last two starts, hitting the frame latest when 3rd at Taree Super Track over 300m. The form out of her last race has been franked. Leading chance. LUMEAH MATILDA (2) was in the minors two back (20.15) at this track but ran below best last time there, finishing 6th. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Likely to play a prominent role. BORN FEARLESS (1) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
